"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIs the government taking the right approach to reduce heat \nenergy demand?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nEngaging consumers\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFuel poor consumers\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nImpact on bills\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nElectrically-heated homes\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nArea-based schemes \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat progress is the government making on reducing the demand for heat?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;There are sustainability guidelines for biomass, do these go far enough?&#xa0;&#xa0;What are the relative merits of using gas to directly provide space heating compared to centralised electricity production plus domestic heat pumps?  &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nCosts – running and installation\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nVariance in carbon savings\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nGrid capacity\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Why is community heating/CHP not more common in the UK?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nShould the government take any further any specific actions in relation to cooling? &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhy does the RHI not seem to promote heat pumps successfully/\nHow successful will the RHI be when rolled out to households?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nMeasures to promote new heating technologies\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n              \nThermal storage is a potential useful method of balancing electricity/energy demand both diurnally and annually.  What is government policy doing to promote thermal storage, and should it do more/different?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSeptember 2013\n&#xa0;\n Consumer Focus, 2013, Submission to the Energy and Climate Change Committee, Green Deal watching brief, \nhttp://\nwww.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmselect/cmenergy/142/142we10.htm\n \nUK-GBC Task Group Report: Retrofit Incentives, http://www.ukgbc.org/resources/publication/uk-gbc-task-group-report-retrofit-incentives\n \nConsumer Futures is currently carrying \nout a research project looking at how such an initiative could work.\n Consumer Focus/William Baker, 2011, Off-gas consumers: Information on households without mains gas heating, \nhttp://www.consumerfocus.org.uk/publications/off-gas-consumers-information-on-households-without-mains-gas-heating\n \n Consumer Futures, 2013, the Hardest Hit, \nhttp://www.consumerfutures.org.uk/reports/the-hardest-hit-going-beyond-the-mean-a-report-by-cse-on-the-impact-of-energy-policy-on-consumers-\nbills\n&#xa0;\n \nProgramme stats for previous Scottish energy efficiency programmes have been published here: http://www.energysavingtrust.org.uk/scotland/Publications2/Take-action/Home-Energy-Programmes-Detailed-Report-2009-2013-Excel\n \nhttp://www.consumerfocus.org.uk/scotland/publications/keeping-the-heat-in-scotlands-homes\n \nDECC (2012) \nA consultation on proposed changes to the Government’s Standard Assessment Procedure \nhttp://www.bre.co.uk/sap2012/page.jsp?id=2759\n \nConsumer Futures (2\n012) From devotees to the disengaged – time of use tariffs, \nhttp://www.consumerfutures.org.uk/reports/from-devotees-to-the-disengaged-time-of-use-tariffs\n&#xa0;\n"